00:06:03.156 --> 00:06:05.530
So today I'm going to talk to
you about online censorship

00:06:05.530 --> 00:06:06.670
and propaganda in China.

00:06:09.460 --> 00:06:11.830
When we think about
the Chinese government

00:06:11.830 --> 00:06:13.750
and what it does to
control information,

00:06:13.750 --> 00:06:16.870
this is a program that's
obviously designed to suppress,

00:06:16.870 --> 00:06:20.350
to distort, to manipulate,
and to control information,

00:06:20.350 --> 00:06:24.220
but paradoxically it could
actually reveal something to us

00:06:24.220 --> 00:06:27.310
about the intentions and
goals of this opaque regime.

00:06:27.310 --> 00:06:29.740
When we collect
this data at scale,

00:06:29.740 --> 00:06:31.710
and when we observe
this data at scale.

00:06:31.710 --> 00:06:33.574
And so this is where
data science comes in.

00:06:33.574 --> 00:06:35.740
And I feel like the term
data science-- sometimes we

00:06:35.740 --> 00:06:36.430
use science.

00:06:36.430 --> 00:06:38.830
Sometimes they use computational
social science machine

00:06:38.830 --> 00:06:39.730
learning.

00:06:39.730 --> 00:06:42.880
What we mean is using tools
that analyze large scale data,

00:06:42.880 --> 00:06:46.090
or at least that's
what I'm talking about.

00:06:46.090 --> 00:06:48.460
The work I'm talking
to you about today

00:06:48.460 --> 00:06:51.010
is a series from a
series of three papers.

00:06:51.010 --> 00:06:53.290
The first is the
observational study

00:06:53.290 --> 00:06:55.330
of how the Chinese
government removes

00:06:55.330 --> 00:06:57.170
content from social media.

00:06:57.170 --> 00:06:59.650
The second is an
experiment that establishes

00:06:59.650 --> 00:07:03.550
a causal linkage between what
people post and what's removed.

00:07:03.550 --> 00:07:09.340
And the third is a paper that's
looking at online propaganda.

00:07:09.340 --> 00:07:12.850
And what I mean by that is
how the government fabricates

00:07:12.850 --> 00:07:16.060
social media content as
if it were the opinions

00:07:16.060 --> 00:07:18.880
of ordinary people.

00:07:18.880 --> 00:07:21.520
Starting with online
censorship, there

00:07:21.520 --> 00:07:27.010
are rumors of as many as
200,000 workers in China working

00:07:27.010 --> 00:07:30.250
for firms like Tencent,
Alibaba, [? Signa, ?]

00:07:30.250 --> 00:07:35.470
whose whole jobs is to
censor and remove content.

00:07:35.470 --> 00:07:38.170
A lot of the work
is manual aided by--

00:07:38.170 --> 00:07:39.470
aided by technology.

00:07:39.470 --> 00:07:41.650
But there is-- at least
the perception is--

00:07:41.650 --> 00:07:44.920
or belief that there is a
human oversight into what

00:07:44.920 --> 00:07:46.840
is or is not removed.

00:07:46.840 --> 00:07:49.180
And there are some
who think that maybe

00:07:49.180 --> 00:07:52.210
China's efforts to censor
represents the largest

00:07:52.210 --> 00:07:55.430
selective suppression of human
expression in recorded history.

00:07:55.430 --> 00:07:57.730
So that sounds really
big, but at the same time

00:07:57.730 --> 00:08:01.360
we have more and more data
recorded about our lives

00:08:01.360 --> 00:08:03.790
now than ever before.

00:08:03.790 --> 00:08:07.090
How we studied censorship
is we gathered millions

00:08:07.090 --> 00:08:09.580
of social media posts the
instant they appeared,

00:08:09.580 --> 00:08:11.770
so before the government
and the social media

00:08:11.770 --> 00:08:14.350
sites could censor them, from
a lot of different social media

00:08:14.350 --> 00:08:15.760
sites.

00:08:15.760 --> 00:08:18.160
And then we went back carefully
to each of these posts

00:08:18.160 --> 00:08:19.960
later on to see if
it was censored,

00:08:19.960 --> 00:08:22.210
and we did this in
an automated fashion.

00:08:22.210 --> 00:08:24.580
And censorship is very clear.

00:08:24.580 --> 00:08:26.470
You see these sorts
of messages that say,

00:08:26.470 --> 00:08:27.970
sorry, the host you
were looking for

00:08:27.970 --> 00:08:30.817
does not exist, has been deleted
or is being investigated.

00:08:30.817 --> 00:08:33.400
Or this is the good one, which
is like, the page you requested

00:08:33.400 --> 00:08:35.770
is not here, but why don't
you go look at something else

00:08:35.770 --> 00:08:37.780
instead.

00:08:37.780 --> 00:08:41.230
So we were clearly able
to detect censorship.

00:08:41.230 --> 00:08:45.370
And what we came across when we
looked at the previous research

00:08:45.370 --> 00:08:47.890
on what we thought about
censorship in China

00:08:47.890 --> 00:08:51.100
is that the belief was that
China would censor everything

00:08:51.100 --> 00:08:54.250
that was bad for the
government, bad for the state,

00:08:54.250 --> 00:08:55.090
bad for the regime.

00:08:55.090 --> 00:08:56.230
That could be criticism.

00:08:56.230 --> 00:08:59.200
That could be things about
protest or collective action.

00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:01.030
What we find is that
this is not the case.

00:09:01.030 --> 00:09:04.150
China censors something much
more narrow and specific,

00:09:04.150 --> 00:09:07.990
which is just about censoring
to stop collective action.

00:09:07.990 --> 00:09:09.880
When I use the term
collective action,

00:09:09.880 --> 00:09:12.670
I mean people getting
together in the real world

00:09:12.670 --> 00:09:14.600
to do something.

00:09:14.600 --> 00:09:16.600
A lot of times
this is protesting

00:09:16.600 --> 00:09:20.290
against the government, but
it doesn't always have to be.

00:09:20.290 --> 00:09:22.450
And at the same time,
while censorship

00:09:22.450 --> 00:09:24.500
is focused on stopping
collective action,

00:09:24.500 --> 00:09:29.050
there's a lot of criticism
that still flourishes online.

00:09:29.050 --> 00:09:31.700
When we talk about
social media in China,

00:09:31.700 --> 00:09:35.470
as well as other places, we
usually talk about burstiness.

00:09:35.470 --> 00:09:40.360
So certain things will trend
at certain points in time.

00:09:40.360 --> 00:09:42.690
But what also is interesting
in the Chinese cases is

00:09:42.690 --> 00:09:44.440
that censorship is also bursty.

00:09:44.440 --> 00:09:47.890
So in this plot, the x-axis
is a six-month time frame.

00:09:47.890 --> 00:09:51.610
The y-axis is a sample
of count of posts.

00:09:51.610 --> 00:09:54.220
So in the gray are
just number of posts

00:09:54.220 --> 00:09:56.320
by day over the
six month period.

00:09:56.320 --> 00:09:59.277
And red are all the
posts that are deleted.

00:09:59.277 --> 00:10:01.110
And what you can see
is that everything here

00:10:01.110 --> 00:10:03.070
is about a city
in southern China

00:10:03.070 --> 00:10:04.870
called, [INAUDIBLE]
known for its lichees

00:10:04.870 --> 00:10:06.460
and textile manufacturing.

00:10:06.460 --> 00:10:10.240
In June of this particular year,
there was a large scale migrant

00:10:10.240 --> 00:10:11.740
worker protest.

00:10:11.740 --> 00:10:14.080
There was a corresponding
burst of discussion

00:10:14.080 --> 00:10:17.080
online about this city
because of the protests,

00:10:17.080 --> 00:10:19.550
and there's also this
burst of censorship.

00:10:19.550 --> 00:10:21.430
So the unit that
we're interested in

00:10:21.430 --> 00:10:26.950
is not topics and not posts,
it's these bursts of discussion

00:10:26.950 --> 00:10:30.500
because the censorship is
happening in these bursts.

00:10:30.500 --> 00:10:33.670
So some bursts are censored,
but not all bursts are censored.

00:10:33.670 --> 00:10:35.020
This is the same type of plot.

00:10:35.020 --> 00:10:38.360
Six-month time period,
count on the y-axis.

00:10:38.360 --> 00:10:41.430
But everyone here is
talking about power prices.

00:10:41.430 --> 00:10:44.380
In this particular frame,
there was a heat wave.

00:10:44.380 --> 00:10:47.292
At the same time, the government
increased power prices.

00:10:47.292 --> 00:10:49.750
So there are a lot of people
complaining online about this,

00:10:49.750 --> 00:10:51.576
and that's the
burst you see here.

00:10:51.576 --> 00:10:53.200
But you don't see a
corresponding burst

00:10:53.200 --> 00:10:55.130
in censorship.

00:10:55.130 --> 00:10:58.100
So our hypothesis going in is
that the Chinese government

00:10:58.100 --> 00:11:02.090
is censoring all the posts in
these volume bursts associated

00:11:02.090 --> 00:11:04.890
with events with collective
action potential.

00:11:04.890 --> 00:11:07.760
It doesn't really matter
what the post is saying.

00:11:07.760 --> 00:11:11.510
It matters what the overall
discussion is about.

00:11:11.510 --> 00:11:14.580
And we test this in a
couple of different ways.

00:11:14.580 --> 00:11:16.460
So one test we do
is to look at what

00:11:16.460 --> 00:11:18.920
are the events
precipitating these bursts,

00:11:18.920 --> 00:11:22.910
and then to categorize these
events into news, policy,

00:11:22.910 --> 00:11:24.680
collective action, and others.

00:11:24.680 --> 00:11:26.540
And we create a
measure, something

00:11:26.540 --> 00:11:28.190
we call censorship magnitude.

00:11:28.190 --> 00:11:31.040
This is the intensity of
censorship in these bursts as

00:11:31.040 --> 00:11:32.540
opposed to outside.

00:11:32.540 --> 00:11:35.340
And you can see that for the
most part, these births related

00:11:35.340 --> 00:11:37.880
to policy and news, which are
purple and blue, in the darker

00:11:37.880 --> 00:11:41.630
colors, have a censorship
magnitude around zero, which

00:11:41.630 --> 00:11:44.662
means that there's really
no increase in censorship

00:11:44.662 --> 00:11:45.620
when the bursts happen.

00:11:45.620 --> 00:11:47.161
Sometimes there's
actually a decrease

00:11:47.161 --> 00:11:50.460
because there's a burst that
maybe less content is removed.

00:11:50.460 --> 00:11:53.090
But when you look, there's
a big long right tail,

00:11:53.090 --> 00:11:55.130
and a lot of these are in red.

00:11:55.130 --> 00:11:57.800
So all the kind of
little segments in red

00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:00.150
are events or bursts related
to collective action,

00:12:00.150 --> 00:12:03.090
and that's where the censorship
magnitude is much higher.

00:12:03.090 --> 00:12:05.840
We also see that in the
yellow pornography a censored.

00:12:05.840 --> 00:12:08.540
That's less interesting
for our particular focus

00:12:08.540 --> 00:12:12.490
because every country to some
extent censors pornography.

00:12:12.490 --> 00:12:14.660
But we go a step
further, not just looking

00:12:14.660 --> 00:12:16.910
at the kind of discussion--
overall discussion

00:12:16.910 --> 00:12:19.880
of the bursts, but what
each post is saying.

00:12:19.880 --> 00:12:23.450
And there we see that regardless
of the content or sentiment

00:12:23.450 --> 00:12:26.240
of the posts, what really
matters as censorship

00:12:26.240 --> 00:12:28.700
is the overall discussion.

00:12:28.700 --> 00:12:31.400
So into this plot, the y-axis
is the percent censored.

00:12:31.400 --> 00:12:34.640
On the left panel, these
are posts in bursts

00:12:34.640 --> 00:12:36.440
related to collective action.

00:12:36.440 --> 00:12:39.080
And they're whether the post
is critical of the state in red

00:12:39.080 --> 00:12:40.910
or support of the
state and green.

00:12:40.910 --> 00:12:43.080
It's highly censored
versus posts

00:12:43.080 --> 00:12:46.690
that are happening in bursts not
related to collective action.

00:12:46.690 --> 00:12:49.250
There, whether you're critical
or not doesn't really matter.

00:12:49.250 --> 00:12:51.360
The censorship is very low.

00:12:51.360 --> 00:12:54.230
So censorship or this
removing of content

00:12:54.230 --> 00:12:56.330
seems really focused
on collective action.

00:12:56.330 --> 00:12:58.710
What happens with
online propaganda?

00:12:58.710 --> 00:13:01.290
We can think of propaganda as
kind of reverse censorship.

00:13:01.290 --> 00:13:04.370
Instead of taking away
we're adding information.

00:13:04.370 --> 00:13:08.480
And here, I'm talking about
the specific form of propaganda

00:13:08.480 --> 00:13:12.110
that's the fabrication of
content by the government

00:13:12.110 --> 00:13:14.400
as if it was the opinions
of ordinary people.

00:13:14.400 --> 00:13:16.700
So sometimes this is called
government astro-turfing.

00:13:16.700 --> 00:13:19.720
It can be called misinformation
campaigns, disinformation,

00:13:19.720 --> 00:13:20.450
trolling.

00:13:20.450 --> 00:13:22.460
There are lots of
different names and words

00:13:22.460 --> 00:13:24.620
that people are using
for these phenomenon.

00:13:24.620 --> 00:13:28.430
In the Chinese context, the
people who do this type of work

00:13:28.430 --> 00:13:32.390
are known officially as internet
commentators, [INAUDIBLE]..

00:13:32.390 --> 00:13:34.350
So it's a very innocuous name.

00:13:34.350 --> 00:13:37.620
But more colloquially, they're
known as 50 cent party members.

00:13:37.620 --> 00:13:40.880
People who are paid piecemeal
$0.50 for each post that they

00:13:40.880 --> 00:13:42.980
make online.

00:13:42.980 --> 00:13:44.055
And so what do they do?

00:13:44.055 --> 00:13:46.430
The prevailing view-- and this
is my view before all this

00:13:46.430 --> 00:13:49.130
research-- is that these
50 cent party members--

00:13:49.130 --> 00:13:52.110
I'm just going to call them
that for the rest of the talk--

00:13:52.110 --> 00:13:55.220
that they are arguing with
and debating against those

00:13:55.220 --> 00:13:56.780
who criticize China.

00:13:56.780 --> 00:14:00.680
So let's say, online someone
is criticizing Chinese leaders,

00:14:00.680 --> 00:14:03.410
Chinese policies, or
being really favorable

00:14:03.410 --> 00:14:06.170
of the US or democracy,
50 cent party members

00:14:06.170 --> 00:14:08.480
will come in and argue
against those people.

00:14:08.480 --> 00:14:11.540
That was my belief of what
50 cent party members do.

00:14:11.540 --> 00:14:13.490
But with our research,
what we found

00:14:13.490 --> 00:14:15.950
is that that's not at
all what's going on.

00:14:15.950 --> 00:14:18.060
These 50 cent party
members do not argue.

00:14:18.060 --> 00:14:20.720
They don't even touch
these controversial issues.

00:14:20.720 --> 00:14:22.310
And instead,
they're distracting.

00:14:22.310 --> 00:14:25.400
They're putting out lots of
really positive, happy content

00:14:25.400 --> 00:14:27.320
that's totally
irrelevant, does not

00:14:27.320 --> 00:14:30.740
touch on any critical,
controversial, debatable

00:14:30.740 --> 00:14:32.360
issues.

00:14:32.360 --> 00:14:36.140
And the way we study that is to
try to get ground-truth data.

00:14:36.140 --> 00:14:37.820
So this is hidden--

00:14:37.820 --> 00:14:39.950
this is fabricating
content and trying

00:14:39.950 --> 00:14:41.580
to pretend it's real people.

00:14:41.580 --> 00:14:45.430
So this is not a public program.

00:14:45.430 --> 00:14:48.320
And ground truth data has
been difficult to come by,

00:14:48.320 --> 00:14:52.100
but we were lucky that
a few years ago there

00:14:52.100 --> 00:14:54.840
was a leaked email archive from
the jungle internet propaganda

00:14:54.840 --> 00:14:55.340
office.

00:14:55.340 --> 00:14:58.640
This is one county in
southern South Central China

00:14:58.640 --> 00:15:01.070
where these e-mails
were leaked, and you

00:15:01.070 --> 00:15:04.127
see lots of emails sent to
and from this jungle internet

00:15:04.127 --> 00:15:05.960
propaganda office, which
was in this network

00:15:05.960 --> 00:15:07.460
plot in the middle.

00:15:07.460 --> 00:15:10.490
And all around it
are lots of e-mails

00:15:10.490 --> 00:15:14.540
coming in by internet
commentators claiming credit

00:15:14.540 --> 00:15:17.580
for the posts they've made
on behalf of the government.

00:15:17.580 --> 00:15:19.910
So this is the
ground truth data,

00:15:19.910 --> 00:15:22.410
and it's publicly available now.

00:15:22.410 --> 00:15:24.230
But it has been
largely overlooked

00:15:24.230 --> 00:15:26.410
because it's really messy.

00:15:26.410 --> 00:15:28.070
The e-mails are in
different formats.

00:15:28.070 --> 00:15:31.140
Some of these credit
claiming as a screenshot.

00:15:31.140 --> 00:15:32.880
Some are attachments.

00:15:32.880 --> 00:15:35.810
And what we do is use a lot
of different machine learning

00:15:35.810 --> 00:15:39.170
as well as large scale
hand annotating methods

00:15:39.170 --> 00:15:41.870
to extract and make
this data systematic.

00:15:41.870 --> 00:15:46.370
And from this data we extracted
over 40,000 known 50 cent party

00:15:46.370 --> 00:15:47.360
posts.

00:15:47.360 --> 00:15:50.720
Over 43,000 known posts.

00:15:50.720 --> 00:15:52.880
And so that's what I mean
by ground-truth data.

00:15:52.880 --> 00:15:56.270
We know that these are workers
making these fake posts

00:15:56.270 --> 00:16:00.060
at the behest of the government.

00:16:00.060 --> 00:16:02.780
And then we build out
from this ground-truth

00:16:02.780 --> 00:16:05.760
to extrapolate and
make predictions.

00:16:05.760 --> 00:16:07.790
So first we analyze the
content of the leaked

00:16:07.790 --> 00:16:10.760
data, which is as I mentioned,
from one county in China.

00:16:10.760 --> 00:16:15.030
And then we extrapolate to
all 2,800 counties in China.

00:16:15.030 --> 00:16:16.910
And then we validate
that extrapolation,

00:16:16.910 --> 00:16:18.650
and we also validate
our validation.

00:16:21.260 --> 00:16:25.200
What we're interested in is the
content of these 50 cent party

00:16:25.200 --> 00:16:25.700
posts.

00:16:25.700 --> 00:16:27.920
We want to know what
are they saying.

00:16:27.920 --> 00:16:30.140
And so we estimate the
distribution of these posts

00:16:30.140 --> 00:16:31.652
into five categories.

00:16:31.652 --> 00:16:33.110
The first category
is what we call,

00:16:33.110 --> 00:16:34.470
taunting of foreign countries.

00:16:34.470 --> 00:16:36.470
So this is criticizing
people online

00:16:36.470 --> 00:16:38.540
who are supporting the
US, supporting democracy,

00:16:38.540 --> 00:16:40.070
supporting the west.

00:16:40.070 --> 00:16:42.590
The second is what we
call argumentative praise

00:16:42.590 --> 00:16:43.760
and criticism.

00:16:43.760 --> 00:16:45.920
So these are people who
are critical of those

00:16:45.920 --> 00:16:48.140
who are critical of
China, China's policies,

00:16:48.140 --> 00:16:50.820
and then praising those
who endorse China.

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:53.520
The third category we call
non-argumentative praise

00:16:53.520 --> 00:16:54.400
or suggestions.

00:16:54.400 --> 00:16:59.390
So this is statements like,
we should increase prosperity

00:16:59.390 --> 00:17:01.760
or we should improve
the plight of the poor.

00:17:01.760 --> 00:17:05.750
Things at such a general level
that everyone can agree with.

00:17:05.750 --> 00:17:07.569
The third category
is just announcements

00:17:07.569 --> 00:17:09.140
of policies and programs.

00:17:09.140 --> 00:17:11.560
And the fourth is this
cheer leading category.

00:17:11.560 --> 00:17:14.599
So motivational, inspirational,
positive messages.

00:17:14.599 --> 00:17:17.240
You get messages like,
I woke up this morning

00:17:17.240 --> 00:17:21.079
feeling so thankful that
I'm a Chinese citizen.

00:17:21.079 --> 00:17:23.390
I hope everyone else
has a wonderful day.

00:17:23.390 --> 00:17:26.180
So just being very,
very positive and happy.

00:17:26.180 --> 00:17:28.730
Not touching on any
sort of content.

00:17:28.730 --> 00:17:31.454
Prevailing view is that this
is what the 50 cent party

00:17:31.454 --> 00:17:32.120
member is doing.

00:17:32.120 --> 00:17:34.880
This taunting, this
argumentation, debating.

00:17:34.880 --> 00:17:37.070
And what we find
is all the content

00:17:37.070 --> 00:17:38.744
falls into these
three categories.

00:17:38.744 --> 00:17:40.160
And I'm going to
show you analysis

00:17:40.160 --> 00:17:43.220
from five data sets that
move from the leaked data

00:17:43.220 --> 00:17:46.040
out to other places in China.

00:17:46.040 --> 00:17:49.250
And so this plot on the
y-axis is just the proportion

00:17:49.250 --> 00:17:51.410
of content in each of
these five categories

00:17:51.410 --> 00:17:53.780
that I just showed you,
which our labeled here.

00:17:53.780 --> 00:17:56.795
The starting data set is these
posts from the leaked e-mails.

00:17:56.795 --> 00:17:59.000
This 43,000 posts from
the leaked e-mails.

00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:01.400
They're made to all sorts
of websites in China.

00:18:01.400 --> 00:18:06.080
And here, over 80% of the
content is in cheer leading.

00:18:06.080 --> 00:18:07.680
And that was really
surprising to us,

00:18:07.680 --> 00:18:10.090
because we thought
the content would

00:18:10.090 --> 00:18:12.920
be like down here in
taunting argumentation,

00:18:12.920 --> 00:18:14.060
and that wasn't the case.

00:18:14.060 --> 00:18:15.590
And we think this
is very unlikely

00:18:15.590 --> 00:18:18.020
to be due to any sort
of sampling error.

00:18:18.020 --> 00:18:20.330
But we push really
hard and try to find

00:18:20.330 --> 00:18:23.030
any content that would go into
the taunting argumentation

00:18:23.030 --> 00:18:23.880
categories.

00:18:23.880 --> 00:18:27.110
And in the end, we found,
I think, 26 posts out

00:18:27.110 --> 00:18:32.041
of 43,000 that could conceivably
be in those categories.

00:18:32.041 --> 00:18:34.040
So the next thing we do,
we want to extrapolate.

00:18:34.040 --> 00:18:35.930
The next thing we do
to set up for that

00:18:35.930 --> 00:18:38.390
is to look just at
posts made on Weibo,

00:18:38.390 --> 00:18:41.530
which is the Chinese kind
of version of Twitter.

00:18:41.530 --> 00:18:43.622
And we're looking at posts
from all the accounts

00:18:43.622 --> 00:18:44.330
that were leaked.

00:18:44.330 --> 00:18:47.120
So this is about
now 160,000 posts.

00:18:47.120 --> 00:18:53.180
And again, primarily the content
is focused on cheer leading.

00:18:53.180 --> 00:18:55.610
When we looked at
these Weibo accounts,

00:18:55.610 --> 00:18:58.160
we found that there are
two types of accounts.

00:18:58.160 --> 00:19:00.966
One, where what we
call ordinary accounts.

00:19:00.966 --> 00:19:02.840
These are accounts that
you and I might have.

00:19:02.840 --> 00:19:05.570
They're posting on
food, travel, kids.

00:19:05.570 --> 00:19:07.640
And the intersperse
are a few posts

00:19:07.640 --> 00:19:09.650
made at the behest
of the government.

00:19:09.650 --> 00:19:12.860
So it's incredibly difficult
to identify these accounts that

00:19:12.860 --> 00:19:15.290
are making these posts
because there are actually

00:19:15.290 --> 00:19:17.030
people's normal accounts.

00:19:17.030 --> 00:19:18.920
Oh, and I should say
that the people who

00:19:18.920 --> 00:19:22.700
are making these posts, we found
in the process of systematizing

00:19:22.700 --> 00:19:25.524
the data, were basically
all government employees who

00:19:25.524 --> 00:19:28.190
have other jobs, who are working
for the county, who are working

00:19:28.190 --> 00:19:30.210
for the township,
villages, neighborhoods,

00:19:30.210 --> 00:19:32.450
but who are making
these posts on the side.

00:19:32.450 --> 00:19:34.910
And so some of them were using
their real Weibo accounts

00:19:34.910 --> 00:19:36.200
and making these posts.

00:19:36.200 --> 00:19:37.940
Very difficult to identify.

00:19:37.940 --> 00:19:40.100
But there are also accounts
that were what we call,

00:19:40.100 --> 00:19:44.430
exclusive accounts made just
to make these 50 cent posts.

00:19:44.430 --> 00:19:46.370
These are much
easier to identify,

00:19:46.370 --> 00:19:49.700
and reassuringly, ordinary
and exclusive accounts

00:19:49.700 --> 00:19:51.180
do very similar things.

00:19:51.180 --> 00:19:53.334
So is not the case
that ordinary accounts

00:19:53.334 --> 00:19:55.250
are doing the taunting
and argumentation while

00:19:55.250 --> 00:19:57.200
exclusive accounts of
doing cheer leading.

00:19:57.200 --> 00:20:00.440
And we're going to extrapolate
and predict focusing just

00:20:00.440 --> 00:20:03.530
on these exclusive accounts,
so that's important for us.

00:20:03.530 --> 00:20:05.960
We first start within
county prediction

00:20:05.960 --> 00:20:08.450
and then move to out
of county prediction.

00:20:08.450 --> 00:20:10.630
And the picture is
very, very consistent.

00:20:10.630 --> 00:20:15.290
50 cent party content is
focused on cheer leading,

00:20:15.290 --> 00:20:18.740
these positive
inspirational messages.

00:20:18.740 --> 00:20:20.840
The other thing to note
is that these posts

00:20:20.840 --> 00:20:24.230
are not made uniformly over
time, but are very bursty.

00:20:24.230 --> 00:20:25.800
This is from the leaked data.

00:20:25.800 --> 00:20:28.820
They're making posts
before certain holidays,

00:20:28.820 --> 00:20:31.630
before sensitive political
meetings, web protests,

00:20:31.630 --> 00:20:33.560
and collective action
might be more likely,

00:20:33.560 --> 00:20:36.830
as well as after events,
collective action events, that

00:20:36.830 --> 00:20:39.400
get a lot of national
attention like the [INAUDIBLE]

00:20:39.400 --> 00:20:41.600
or [INAUDIBLE]
railway explosion.

00:20:41.600 --> 00:20:43.670
So it seems that these--

00:20:43.670 --> 00:20:45.410
especially the cheer
leading content

00:20:45.410 --> 00:20:49.870
is aimed or timed to distract
from collective action,

00:20:49.870 --> 00:20:52.310
at least to a certain extent.

00:20:52.310 --> 00:20:54.410
So how do we validate
our predictions?

00:20:54.410 --> 00:20:56.820
We decided to ask the
people we predicted

00:20:56.820 --> 00:20:58.240
to be 50 cent party members.

00:20:58.240 --> 00:21:00.000
You might think, how
is it going to work?

00:21:00.000 --> 00:21:03.032
These people's jobs
are to mislead.

00:21:03.032 --> 00:21:04.240
They work for the government.

00:21:04.240 --> 00:21:05.530
Maybe their jobs are at stake.

00:21:05.530 --> 00:21:08.790
They're not your optimal
survey respondents.

00:21:08.790 --> 00:21:11.930
But we decided to do it
anyway, and we administered

00:21:11.930 --> 00:21:15.120
a double blind survey on
Weibo through direct messaging

00:21:15.120 --> 00:21:16.954
where we said,
ask this question.

00:21:16.954 --> 00:21:18.870
I saw your comment, and
it's really inspiring.

00:21:18.870 --> 00:21:21.119
I want to ask, do you have
any public opinion guidance

00:21:21.119 --> 00:21:23.790
management or online
commenting experience?

00:21:23.790 --> 00:21:26.130
So we're not using the
terminology 50 cent,

00:21:26.130 --> 00:21:28.981
we're using the government's
own terminology.

00:21:28.981 --> 00:21:31.230
So we asked this question
of the accounts we predicted

00:21:31.230 --> 00:21:32.800
to be 50 cent accounts.

00:21:32.800 --> 00:21:34.770
We also asked the same
question of the accounts

00:21:34.770 --> 00:21:36.590
we know to be 50 cent accounts.

00:21:36.590 --> 00:21:38.910
And then we asked the
accounts the same question

00:21:38.910 --> 00:21:41.370
that are unlikely to
be 50 cent accounts.

00:21:41.370 --> 00:21:43.200
And we find that in
the predicted accounts,

00:21:43.200 --> 00:21:46.790
59% say, yes, they do have
this experience and training.

00:21:46.790 --> 00:21:49.890
In the known accounts,
57% say, yes.

00:21:49.890 --> 00:21:53.010
And in the accounts unlikely
to be 50 cent from our method,

00:21:53.010 --> 00:21:54.872
only 19% say, yes.

00:21:54.872 --> 00:21:56.580
And the difference
between the first two,

00:21:56.580 --> 00:21:58.320
the predicted and
the known, there's

00:21:58.320 --> 00:22:01.620
no significant difference
between that response rate.

00:22:01.620 --> 00:22:04.810
So asking the
predicted accounts,

00:22:04.810 --> 00:22:06.150
that's our validation.

00:22:06.150 --> 00:22:08.730
And then asking the known
and unlikely accounts

00:22:08.730 --> 00:22:12.030
is our validation
of the validation.

00:22:12.030 --> 00:22:15.180
So altogether, China's strategy
in censorship and propaganda

00:22:15.180 --> 00:22:17.920
can be reduced to
very simple rules.

00:22:17.920 --> 00:22:20.700
The first is do not engage
on controversial issues.

00:22:20.700 --> 00:22:22.150
Don't censor criticism.

00:22:22.150 --> 00:22:23.430
Don't argue against critics.

00:22:23.430 --> 00:22:27.660
Don't touch kind of people's
real opinions and thoughts

00:22:27.660 --> 00:22:30.440
about policies, the
leaders, and the state.

00:22:30.440 --> 00:22:32.590
And the second is to
stop collective action.

00:22:32.590 --> 00:22:35.340
So censor discussions
of collective action

00:22:35.340 --> 00:22:37.300
that are going
online, and then try

00:22:37.300 --> 00:22:40.170
to distract with this cheer
leading positive content

00:22:40.170 --> 00:22:43.410
after collective action
happens or before time periods

00:22:43.410 --> 00:22:45.270
when collective
action might happen.

00:22:45.270 --> 00:22:47.460
And I think altogether
for a social scientist

00:22:47.460 --> 00:22:50.400
like me is the promise
of data science

00:22:50.400 --> 00:22:54.005
is that when we study
these phenomena at scale,

00:22:54.005 --> 00:22:56.130
government information
control efforts leave really

00:22:56.130 --> 00:22:57.104
big footprints.

00:22:57.104 --> 00:22:58.770
Before, we couldn't
see these footprints

00:22:58.770 --> 00:23:00.600
so we couldn't really
understand what

00:23:00.600 --> 00:23:03.350
these opaque, non-democratic
governments were doing.

00:23:03.350 --> 00:23:05.974
But with data science and
computational data science

00:23:05.974 --> 00:23:07.890
machine learning, whatever
we want to call it,

00:23:07.890 --> 00:23:10.290
these methods allow
us to see things that

00:23:10.290 --> 00:23:12.289
were not visible to us before.

00:23:12.289 --> 00:23:13.080
So I'll stop there.

00:23:13.080 --> 00:23:14.329
Thank you very much.

00:23:14.329 --> 00:23:21.320
[APPLAUSE]

00:23:21.320 --> 00:23:22.720
- Yes, questions?

00:23:22.720 --> 00:23:23.553
- Yes.

00:23:23.553 --> 00:23:24.427
- So, take questions.

00:23:24.427 --> 00:23:25.650
Go ahead.

00:23:25.650 --> 00:23:30.876
- So I was wondering whether
you guys have thought about what

00:23:30.876 --> 00:23:35.260
Chinese government might be
doing [INAUDIBLE] data and how

00:23:35.260 --> 00:23:36.635
they might have--

